## ❌ Mistake #1: Client Component Using fetch() Directly

**Frequency:** Common
**Last Occurrence:** -

### Problem
```tsx
"use client"
export function UserList() {
  const [users, setUsers] = useState([])

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch('/api/users')  // ❌ Unnecessary client-side fetch
      .then(res => res.json())
      .then(data => setUsers(data))
  }, [])

  return <ul>{users.map(u => <li key={u.id}>{u.name}</li>)}</ul>
}
```

### Why This Is Wrong
- Adds unnecessary client-side JavaScript
- Worse performance (client-side data fetching)
- SEO issues (content not rendered on server)
- More complex code (useState + useEffect boilerplate)

### Solution
Convert to Server Component:
```tsx
// Remove "use client", make it async
export default async function UserList() {
  const response = await fetch('/api/users')
  const { data } = await response.json()

  return <ul>{data.map(u => <li key={u.id}>{u.name}</li>)}</ul>
}
```

**Detection Command:**
```bash
# Find Client Components fetching data
grep -l '"use client"' src/features/*/components/*.tsx | \
  xargs grep -l "fetch\|axios"
```

