## ❌ Mistake #2: Missing "use client" Directive

**Frequency:** Very Common
**Last Occurrence:** -

### Problem
```tsx
export function SearchForm() {
  const [query, setQuery] = useState('')  // ❌ Error: useState in Server Component

  return <input onChange={e => setQuery(e.target.value)} />
}
```

### Error Message
```
Error: useState only works in Client Components.
Add the "use client" directive at the top of the file to use it.
```

### Solution
```tsx
"use client"  // ✅ Add this line at the very top

export function SearchForm() {
  const [query, setQuery] = useState('')
  return <input onChange={e => setQuery(e.target.value)} />
}
```

**Detection Command:**
```bash
# Find components with hooks but no "use client"
grep -rl "useState\|useEffect\|useCallback" src/features/*/components | \
  xargs grep -L '"use client"'
```

